Warmup problem

If N users and M arms and M >= N, order one by one by simple pigeonhole principle and get that each user gets rewqard 1 at each time step and total reward 
after T steps = N per user and NT total

If N, M s.t. M < N, Then :

Each arm gets at least Floor(N/M) users; in addition 

the first N - M. Floor(N/M) get the remainder of users => their user count is Floor(N/M) + 1


If this floor > 1 == immediate zero reward as EVERY user has a collision by pigonehole prinxiple

In such case, max reward from pigeonholing is : the number of users n with no collisions n = (M - N + M*Floor(N/M)) when Floor(N/M) = 1
total max possible reward after T steps = n.T

if Floor(N/M) > 1 - of course reward for each user = 0 forever
